      <h5>EXERCISE AND FITNESS:</h5>
      <img src="C:\Users\Student.SOC-ITLAB3-29\web\ex1.jpg" width="250" height="250"> <img src="C:\Users\Student.SOC-ITLAB3-29\web\ex.jpg" width="250" height="250"> <img src="C:\Users\Student.SOC-ITLAB3-29\web\ex 3.png" width="250" height="250">
      <p>Physical fitness is to the human body what fine tuning is to an engine. It enables us to
perform up to our potential. Fitness can be described as a condition that helps us look,
feel and do our best.
z Physical fitness involves the performance of the heart and lungs, and the muscles of the
body. And, since what we do with our bodies also affects what we can do with our
minds, fitness influences to some degree qualities such as mental alertness and
emotional stability.</p>
      <p>Exercise can help prevent excess weight gain or help maintain weight loss. When you engage in physical activity, you burn calories. The more intense the activity, the more calories you burn.

Regular trips to the gym are great, but don't worry if you can't find a large chunk of time to exercise every day. Any amount of activity is better than none at all. To reap the benefits of exercise, just get more active throughout your day — take the stairs instead of the elevator or rev up your household chores. Consistency is key.</p>
